names:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Bedingfield","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Suffolk and Norfolk): variant of   Beddingfield  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Beddingfield","meanings":["English (Suffolk): habitational name from Bedingfield in Suffolk. The placename is recorded in Domesday Book as <i>Bedingefelda</i>, from the Old English personal name <i>Bēda</i> + the connective particle <i>-ing-</i> ‘associated with, named after’ + <i>feld</i> ‘open country’."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: The Scripture name, in Hebrew, Adham, signifying 'man;' literally earthy, red earth; Rudolph, however, says the name in Ethiopic means ' to be fair, beautiful.' Hence the nurse-name Addy, little Adam."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":19,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Adam de Bedingfield II was born about 1240, in Bedingfield, Suffolk, England as the son of Sir Adam de Bedingfield I. He married Mary de Ossory about 1263, in Bedingfield, Suffolk, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. He died about 1275, in Bedingfield, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 37, and was buried in Bedingfield, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"about 1240–about 1275":"umbes 1240–umbes 1275","1240–127